1.0 INTRODUCTION
This manual presents the basic policies and procedures that govern SFA Foundation financial
operations. It helps SFA Foundation establish financial controls within the organization to
ensure accuracy, timeliness and completeness of financial data. The manual is generally
used by finance staff, but it can also act as a reference for SFA Foundation Board and SFA
Foundation staff.
1.1 Content, structure and approval of the manual
This manual has been reviewed and approved by the SFA Foundation Board through the
recommendation of the Executive Management Team and Finance, Risk and Audit
Committee. It contains detailed guidelines and rules, which will be applied for the financial
management of SFA Foundation. This manual will lose its effectiveness if it does not
accurately reflect changes and improvements in the accounting system and procedures. The
continuing suggestions and recommendations of the management and staff are essential to
ensure that it accurately reflects actual procedures.
The manual is divided into sections and subsections. Each section deals with the major
aspects of the function and within each section, there are subsections.
