2.5 Accounting for Foreign Currency Transaction
The financial statements for SFA Foundation will be presented in United States Dollars
(US$). Transactions and balances expressed in currencies other than the US dollars are
treated as follows:
a) The transactions during the year are converted into US Dollars at the actual spot rate
where applicable, otherwise at the rate of the last currency conversion. Assets and liabilities
that are expressed in other currencies are translated to US Dollars at the rate of the last
currency conversion. The resulting differences from conversion and translation are dealt
with in the statement of comprehensive income and expenditure in the year in which they
arise.
b) SFA Foundation will mitigate against foreign exchange loss through several measures
• SFA Foundation shall maintain grants received in the currency of the award
• Grants shall be issued to recipients in the currency the award was given to SFA
Foundation
• For operational activities SFA Foundation will only transfer foreign currency to the
local currency as per cash flow needs
• Operational reserves in the bank shall be invested for short term period between 3-
6 months in the currency the funds are held in.
