4.0 FINANCIAL PLANNING AND REPORTING
4.1 Budget Cycles and Basis of Review
4.1.1 Budgeting
The budget is the road map or plan of the organization and can provide direction to meet its
goals and objectives. This section will focus the standard process and philosophies of
preparing and organizational operating budget, and programmatic budget. The key to
appropriate budget preparation is to follow a timeline that will allow plenty of time to draft and
review with all staff and the board.
Figure 2: SFA Foundation Budget Preparation Cycle
The budget will be used as a road map or plan to guide the operations for the budget period.
It is considered to be a continual process and will need to be reviewed and amended as the
organization and situations change. Because it is a continual process, monitoring of the budget
is critical to the success of the organization.
4.2 Budget Review for Administrative/Operational Budget
The Grants Accountant and Financial Accountant shall produce financial reports comparing
actual expenditure against budget at required intervals. The Head of Finance and Grants has
the responsibility to review and approve the reports.
4.3 Financial Year Plan, Budget Approval Steps and Timelines
a) SFA Foundation has two budget categories. These are the core or administration budget,
and the programme budgets
