9.1 The Policy
The Head of Finance or designate shall ensure that all applicable taxes withheld are
filed and remitted to the Kenya Revenue Authority, Internal Revenue Authority and
certificates issued where applicable.
It shall be the Finance Function’s responsibility to ensure that the liability of all applicable
taxes, such as but not limited to value added tax (VAT) and Withholding tax (WHT) are
deducted, recorded, and filed appropriately.
9.2 The Objective
The objective of this policy is to ensure that the SFA Foundation is compliant with
local tax requirements in Kenya and the US. The Finance Function will record,
report and prepare payments for the following forms of taxes:
 Value Added Tax
 Withholding taxes
 Corporate taxes
9.3 The Process
The Head of Finance or designate will perform the following processes regarding taxes:
1. Setup and enter VAT ID (if new supplier) and VAT tax rates
2. Create journal entry to charge purchases net of VAT to cost centres
3. Advise on, and process, payments due to local withholding taxes in accordance with
applicable Kenyan and US Laws
4. Analyse variances
5. Analyse bank statements to identify VAT that is recoverable
6. Follow applicable Kenyan and US Law for invoice requirements (for applicable
countries)
