1.0 PURPOSE
The purpose of this Science for Africa (SFA) Foundation policy is to:-
a) Ensure that travellers on official SFA Foundation business are provided with the resources
needed to accomplish required travel on missions outside of the duty post, and that conditions
of travel are safe, convenient, reasonably comfortable, and as conducive to productive output
as would be the case at the duty station, all things being equal.
b) Ensure travel arrangements result in the least expense to SFA Foundation, providing, that
such arrangements do not result in either ineffective use of the traveller’s work time,
unreasonable inconvenience, or negatively impact the traveller’s safety or health.
2.0 SCOPE
The provisions of the SFA Foundation Travel Policy apply to all SFA Foundation personnel and
SFA Foundation oversight boards engaged in the business of SFA Foundation. The policy covers
official mission travel, training travel, both international and domestic.
2.1 Exclusions
Home leave, initial and relocation travel, and compassionate leave travel polices are detailed in
the SFA Foundation Human Resources Policies Manual
3.0 DEFINITIONS
Programme-related travel
This is travel planned in conjunction with work related to SFA Foundation activities. A staff
member may also attend a professional meeting as a representative of SFA Foundation or when
it is relevant to the staff member’s discipline, interest, or work. Planning for this category of travel
should be done as part of the budgeting process, and the appropriate authority must approve it.
Invitational travel
A staff member may participate, when invited, in meetings and conferences organized by external
agencies. These travel costs are expected to be borne by the inviting organizations. All the details
of this invitation must be approved by the supervisor and should be forwarded to the Head of
Finance and Grants to ensure that the finance department invoices the host organization in the
case that SFA Foundation is expected to purchase ticket and seek reimbursement. Related travel
costs will be charged to staff travel budget until a reimbursement is received.
4.0 ENFORCEMENT OF POLICY
The Head of Finance and Grants will enforce and update this policy.
5.0 POLICY STATEMENT
The following principles are held for all travellers on SFA Foundation mission: -
a) Travel by SFA Foundation staff and office holders is planned, budgeted, and approved by the
relevant authority/budget holder before it is embarked on;
b) Cash advance or preloading of debit cards, where applicable, for travel related expenses are
arranged and provided before travelling;
c) Economy class travel ticket be issued by SFA Foundation contracted agents for all SFA
Foundation official air travels, except where special circumstances require otherwise as per
clause 10.2;
d) The Procurement Unit, the travel and events office and designated Programme Assistants will
