5.1 Roles and responsibilities
a) The traveller is responsible for complying with the travel policy and for obtaining required
approvals as early as possible but before 3 weeks of travel for known planned travel;
b) Supervisors and other positions involved in the approval of travel plans are expected to ensure
any known annual travel plans are presented at the time of budgeting and included in the
annual procurement plan. The travel requests are to be submitted to the procurement office
3 weeks in advance through approved purchase requests;
c) Since SFA Foundation operates on the tenets of Value-For-Money (VfM) i.e. Efficiency,
Economy and Effectiveness, the procurement office to liaise with the Travel and Events Office
to ensure VfM is achieved for all contracts with the service providers;
d) The Head of Finance & Grants or through the procurement unit manages the contracts with
the contracted service providers;
e) The procurement unit to receive and manage all complaints related to service delivery by the
service providers, i.e. travel agents, accommodation providers and taxi services;
f) SFA Foundation has indicative rates for cost of accommodation & meals, the rates are to be
used in determining the travel advance staff should take during travel to cover for
accommodation, meals and incidentals, in the instances where a debit card is not provided.
The rates will be reviewed on a regular basis to reflect the most reasonable cost of living;
g) The Travel and Events Officer assists in visa processing and obtaining travel insurance where
applicable;
h) Finance to provide travel advances and ensure prompt and compliant settlement of expenses;
i) All budget holders are expected to monitor compliance with the travel policies when reviewing
and approving expenses.
