8.0 TRAVEL ADVANCES AND TRAVEL EXPENSES
8.1 Travel advances
Frequent travellers will be issued with corporate debit cards that will be used to pay for
accommodation, local travel and other authorized expenses. Terms and conditions for the use of
the Debit Card are provided to all holders of such cards, and they are expected to abide by them
as per Institutional Debit (prepaid) card policy. In the case the staff member does not have a
debit card issued either because they are new or have not yet been identified as frequent traveller,
travel advance will be given as defined under the finance policy SFA Foundation shall endeavour
to pay for cost of accommodation before travel where possible. If circumstances warrant a
reasonably higher amount and the traveller has no access to a debit card, the traveller may make
a request to the Head of Department or their delegated authority and in their absence the Head
of Finance and Grants or Executive Director in that order, citing the reasons for the additional
amount.
The travel advance request will be made on the finance system (All SFA Foundation staff have
access to the travel module on the finance system), the TA number will be issued automatically
by the system.
Additional travel advances will not be provided if a travel advance remains outstanding (i.e., no
travel expense claim has been filed and no unused cash has been reimbursed). Exceptions may
be possible under certain circumstances, such as if the traveller must make sequential trips with
less than 5 days interval.
8.2 Use of SFA Foundation debit card
All funds loaded into the debit card will be initially charged to the individual’s personal debit card
account and treated as personal transactions until a Travel Expense Report (TER) showing a
detail of all the expenses incurred is submitted to Finance. Expenses made with an SFA
Foundation debit card will be reviewed and audited as per set policy on expenses and the
calculation of what is owed to the traveller by SFA Foundation, or vice-versa, will take into account
the combination of the cash advance and the debit card charges, and entitlements as
expenditures according to the travel policy guidelines. More detailed guidelines on debit card
usage are contained in the SFA Foundation Debit card policies and Procedure manual.
8.3 Submitting Travel Expense Reports
Travellers should maintain a daily record of expenses and all receipts for each expense to
facilitate the filing of a travel expense report immediately upon return to the duty station.
a) If the traveller owes SFA Foundation any funds, those funds should be returned to SFA
Foundation within 10 working days upon return and a receipt obtained;
b) All travel expense reports must be submitted to the Finance Officer within 10 working days
following completion of travel after they have been approved by the supervisor;
c) In the case of back-to-back travel, staff MUST submit their claims before they embark on the
next travel. This applies to those who have at least five working days in the office before the
next travel. Those with shorter times than 5 days, will reconcile the outstanding concurrent
imprest within 10 days of their return from a subsequent journey;
d) Lack of compliance to timely submission of reports shall trigger a deduction of outstanding
amount from payroll. Continuous non-compliance shall be deemed a case of indiscipline and
handled according to the HR manual.
Mandatory documents to attach to the Travel Expense claim include:
 E-ticket;
 Boarding passes;
