9.1 Accommodation
a) SFA Foundation will pay the actual bill for room rent for a single standard room including any
local tax and service charges. The hotel standard rating is country dependent. The overriding
concern for SFA Foundation is for the staff to stay in a comfortable accommodation. The
recommended accommodation rate to be applied to all SFA Foundation staff is as below.
Within Africa on a Bed & Breakfast basis up to US$ 250
Out of Africa on a Bed & Breakfast basis up to US$ 300
The room rate should not exceed the lodging rate for that location. The booking of
accommodation must follow the procurement process and the most affordable hotel within
proper judgement of location, safety and accessibility considered. Exceptions include, for
example, where a traveller is participating in a meeting or training course held at the hotel,
and where other participants are lodged. This should be pre-approved by the Director of
Programmes or the Executive Director;
b) SFA Foundation will provide an incidental allowance which is intended to cover miscellaneous
personal costs such as personal hygiene, clothing including comfort clothing for weather
extremes, home phone calls, evening drinks etc while on out of Country travel. This is applied
to each day of travel including the first and last day. The amount to be given will $20 per travel
day subject to funding grant terms and conditions;
c) If an SFA Foundation employee or other person (family) offers room & board to a visiting SFA
Foundation traveller, he/she may be compensated by the traveller with up to $25 (United State
Dollars Twenty-Five Only) per night for the first 7 days only. Such an arrangement should be
noted on the Travel Expense Report (TER) and pre-approved by the approving authority;
d) SFA Foundation travellers are expected to seek accommodation that is comfortable, clean,
