10.0 INTERNATIONAL AIR TRAVEL
10.1 SFA Foundation travel agents
The SFA Foundation Travel agents will be contracted following a transparent and rigorous
process as per the guidelines contained in the manual for procurement of services. All official
travel will be booked through the SFA Foundation travel agent unless extreme circumstances
warrant otherwise. Those circumstances need to be pre-approved by the Directors or the Head
of Finance and Grants.
SFA Foundation will not take any responsibility, financial or otherwise, for any problem a staff
member may encounter with the on-site travel agent regarding tickets purchased for personal
use.
10.2 Class of travel and types of ticket
Economy/Business class upgrades and ticket flexibility;
 Travel for a duration of less than eight hours: the lowest available airfare in economy class for
the most direct and most economical routing is authorized;
 Travel for a duration over eight hours: the lowest available airfare in business class for the
most direct and economical routing is authorized (more on routing below) this is however
subject to the grant conditions under which the travel is being charged. Where the funder
source is clearly to the contrary, or is SFA Foundation Core funded, the travel will revert to
economy, unless otherwise justified;
 Use of business class travel for less than 8 hours (or over 8 hours as the case may be) must
be approved by the Executive Director through the supervisor. Such cases may be due to
medical condition (a medical report must be provided), back-to-back travel for staff and other
cases for consideration are at the discretion of the Executive Director and must be justified.
In the event that the subject is the Executive Director the Head of Finance and Grants or the
Head of Human Resources and Operations may provide the decision.
If the layover between the flights is more than eight hours a dayroom may be provided – the
continuing leg of the flight will then be economy.
The travel agencies have been instructed to give information on the most affordable flight
available to the traveller among a minimum of three options (whenever feasible).
The particular circumstances of each type of ticket are expected to be presented by the travel
agent but the traveller should also ensure that s/he fully understands the available options and
their consequences.
When an economy ticket is authorized but the traveller wants to travel on business class, travellers
will personally pay the cost of an upgrade to business class or use airline frequent flier points to
do so. Travellers will be required to pay the additional cost for an economy class fare that is
upgradeable to an upgradable economy class or business class with frequent flier points.
The class of travel policy described above is applicable to all SFA Foundation staff, SFA
Foundation fellows travelling for SFA Foundation business and members of the SFA Foundation
Board and other oversight Committees engaged in the business of SFA Foundation
Consultants and interview candidates for employment by SFA Foundation will fly in economy
class unless there are specific conditions in related grant arrangements under which they are
travelling.
