5.0 POLICY STATEMENT
5.1 Principles
SFA Foundation subscribes to the following Principles developed by the International
Development Research Funders designed to uphold the highest standards of Safeguarding.
a) SFA Foundation is committed to strengthen our safeguarding practices and compliance
processes.
b) SFA Foundation will consciously work collectively with our partners in the pan-African
research community to strengthen safeguarding practices and compliance processes on
the continent.
c) As a major pan-African research funder and preferred Science Technology and Innovation
(STI) partner, SFA Foundation condemns all forms of abuse, including bullying and sexual
and other forms of harassment. SFA Foundation takes a zero-tolerance approach to harm
and abuse to any individual employed through or associated with SFA Foundation
programmes in all contexts, whether in humanitarian or fragile and conflict-affected
settings, in other field contexts or within the pan-African or international research
community that we do business with.
d) SFA Foundation recognises that the nature of scientific endeavour in which research
teams may be working with individuals or communities facing systemic vulnerabilities, and
where junior staff may be dependent upon senior staff for mentorship and support, or
where research staff may be engaged on short-term contracts, presents situations in which
abuses of power may occur.
e) SFA Foundation pledges to work on raising standards of behaviour across the research
community on the continent and influence the sector, recognising the strength of existing
good practices and working in partnership with the global research community.
f) SFA Foundation will place utmost importance on the protection from harm and abuse of
all individuals, including research participants and their communities, and those that
volunteer, work (researchers and others) or study in the research sector.
g) SFA Foundation expects research institutions on the continent (universities and other
research entities) to promote a culture in which harm and abuse is less likely to happen,
and to act swiftly to respond to cases that do emerge, in line with international standards.
h) SFA Foundation recognises that tackling bullying, sexual harassment and other forms of
abuse requires a multi-pronged approach, focusing on governance, human resources,
whistleblowing and risk management policies. African research institutions and other SFA
Foundation partner institutions must have systems and policies which support everyone,
integrating clear codes of conduct into processes of recruitment, professional development
and promotion, and ensuring that timely, transparent, robust and fair processes are in
place and accessible by all. It is not acceptable for any allegation to be ignored and SFA
Foundation expects institutions to respond quickly and effectively when allegations are
made.
i) SFA Foundation undertakes, where necessary and appropriate, to introduce, following
consultation, specific clauses into SFA Foundation contracts and terms and conditions,
including requirements that institutions report, at an aggregate level, on incidents occurring
and actions taken. SFA Foundation will reserve the right to terminate institutional and
individual research funding contracts and grants if a breach of safeguarding practice is
proven and to review the eligibility of institutions and individuals to receive major awards.
j) SFA Foundation will adopt an evidence-based approach, implementing change where the
risk and need is greatest. There is an established wealth of knowledge and experience in
research ethics and research integrity. High-quality frameworks and standards are already
in place; Some African research institutions have policies on workplace harassment and
bullying, and well-established ethical review procedures to guide the conduct of research
involving human participants. SFA Foundation will identify, understand and learn from
effective practices, to ensure SFA Foundation and our partners are sufficiently equipped,
to protect all individuals from harm and abuse wherever possible, and to respond
appropriately to any allegations.
k) SFA Foundation aims to strengthen institutional capacity and capability across the
