7.9.2 Quality Cost Based Selection Method
This method is used for selection of consultancy firms. When this method is used, the
following shall apply:
a) Invite consultants to bid through advertisement or RFP using existing or borrowed
list of consultants resulting from an expression of interest(EOI);
b) The process will be the same as of that of selection of individual consultants
discussed above; however, the responsive bidder recommended for award of
contract is the highest ranking of both technical and financial scores combined;
7.9.3 Quality Based Selection
When this method is used, the following shall apply:
a) Invite consultants to bid through advertisement or RFP using existing or borrowed
list of consultants resulting from an expression of interest(EOI);
b) Evaluation of proposals is done to determine eligibility of firm based on technical
capabilities. Firms having the required experience and competence relevant to the
assignment shall be assessed and compared, and the best qualified and
experienced firm shall be selected;
c) Financial negotiations are then done with the highest technical ranking consultant.
7.9.4 Least Cost Selection
When this method is used, the following shall apply:
a) Invite consultants to bid through advertisement or RFP using existing or borrowed
list of consultants resulting from an expression of interest(EOI);
b) Under this method a minimum qualifying mark for the quality is established;
c) Technical proposals are opened first and evaluated and those scoring less than the
minimum qualifying mark as stated in the RFP are rejected;
d) Financial proposals of those meeting the minimum qualifying mark are opened and
the consultant/firm with the lowest price recommended for award and negotiation.
