8.0 VENDOR MANAGEMENT
8.1 Vendor Due diligence
Vendors for each category shall be reviewed at least once every two years. This may be done
in conjunction with a tender process. Pre-qualification or pre-selection shall be based entirely
upon the capability and resources of prospective firms to perform the contract satisfactory. It
shall take into consideration factors and not limited to the following factors:
a) Legal capacity to enter contract by providing a registration/ incorporation certificate.
b) Financial capacity by providing financial statements (Audited accounts and bank
statements);
c) Past experience by indicating where they have conducted similar assignments before
(attach copies of work orders, completion certificates etc.);
d) Litigation history;
e) VAT & Tax compliance certificate to ensure they are meeting the tax obligations;
f) Registration certificates with relevant regulatory bodies; etc.
The Procurement Committee shall drive vendor qualification. The team will also involve
representatives from the user department, relevant program units, Finance, etc. Vendor
qualification will take place in fivestages:
a) Advertisement;
b) Receipt of vendor registration form(s);
c) Registrations forms evaluation/analysis;
d) Field/site visits/reference taking;
e) Short listing.
8.2 Approved Vendor List (AVL)
8.2.1 The Procurement Officer shall maintain a list of qualified vendors, sufficient to ensure
competition by category of goods/services. The AVL shall be maintained in the SFA
Foundation procurement System.
8.2.2 All vendors are subject to a prequalification process and continuous monitoring of their
performance. The Approved Vendor List (AVL) is approved per the authorization
policy and reviewed by the Procurement Committee every three years. The
Procurement Committee makes recommendations on the vendors to be included on
the AVL for approval by the ED. Each selected vendor is requested to fill in SFA
Foundation vendor set up form for approval by the Head of Finance and Grant before
being set in the SFA procurement system.
8.2.3 The Suppliers will be required to provide the following information:
a) Name, email addresses, telephone and fax number, physical address of the
supplier;
b) Type of goods/services they can provide;
c) Any limitation on the list of goods they can provide to SFA Foundation standards;
d) Delivery and payment terms;
e) Start date of the relationship with SFA Foundation;
f) Contact persons;
g) Banking information.
8.3 Suppliers Appraisal/Contract Performance Review
The procurement Officer shall maintain a record of all the contracts issued to suppliers and
appraisal/performance shall be conducted throughout the contract lifetime. Suppliers'
performance appraisal shall be conducted to determine whether SFA Foundation is receiving
the value for money on procurement activities. The criteria to assess vendor performance are
provided in annex 10 of this document. If the results of the evaluation are not up to standards,
the Procurement Unit/ PC meets with the supplier to understand the causes of the problems.
This shall form basis for supplier appraisal, contract extensions or termination of contracts
and de-registration from the AVL. The criterion to vendor assessment shall be as provided in
Annex-10 of this policy document.
