9.0 DISPOSAL OF ASSET
The purpose of this section is to provide guidance on the best practice of disposing assets
that have exhausted their useful life in the organization, obsolete or no longer economical to
maintain. The assets may or may not have been fully depreciated in the books of SFA
Foundation.
9.1 Disposal Methods
All disposals of Assets shall be by sealed bid except where the procurement committee
recommend the following methods:
a) Auction;
b) Sale to staff;
c) Burying, Destruction or Dumping;
d) Donation.
9.1.1 Auction
Requests to Auction SFA Foundation assets shall be submitted to the HFG who shall
seek approval from the ED. Approval will be provided with the understanding that the
auction shall conducted in accordance with established procedures and adherence
as stipulated above. The procurement committee shall conduct the auction of asset
and prepare minutes for the same. The highest unopposed bidder shall be declared
the winner.
9.1.2 Sale to Staff
Requests to sale of SFA Foundation assets to staff, whether by sealed bid, must be
submitted for approval to the Head of Finance/ED or equivalent. Approval will be
provided with the understanding that such sales must be conducted in accordance
with established procedures and adherence to the following:
a) Ensuring that property identified for sale is in excess to the SFA Foundationneeds;
b) Ensuring that all staff are provided with a fair and equitable opportunity to bid for
items on sale;
c) Providing adequate (14 days) notice to staff by announcing the sale on all notice
boards;
d) Full payment before release of asset;
e) Providing the purchaser with a Gate Pass to facilitate removal of the sold property
from the premises;
f) The Finance Division shall confirm, in writing, that the payment in full has been
received, prior to the release of the items sold to respective staff.
9.1.3 Burying, Destruction or Dumping
The DC shall compile a list of materials for disposal. Requests to bury, destroy or,
dump, must be submitted for approval to the Head of Finance/ED or equivalent.
Proper burying, destruction or dumping shall be done in accordance with the law of
the land.
9.1.4 Donation
Requests to donate SFA Foundation assets shall be submitted to the HFG who shall
seek approval from the ED. The donation of asset shall be conducted in a fair and
transparent manner. The procurement committee shall request members of staff to
propose the beneficiary for such items. This can be and not limited to children’s home,
academic institutions etc. The Disposal Committee (DC) shall prepare a list of all the
beneficiaries for vetting. The DC shall conduct due diligence for at least three possible
recipients of donations.
9.2 Disposal Process
9.2.1 A list of the assets to be disposed of must be prepared from which the particulars of
the asset and detailed justification for disposal shall be recorded. The list is prepared
and compiled by the Asset Administration Officer after consultation with the respective
departments whose assets are to be disposed.
