LOGO: PRIMARY OPTION
This is the Science for Africa Foundation logo.
It has been designed to depict the vision and personality of our organisation.
At its core the map of the African continent has been made up of colourful textured segments to represent the diversity and
vibrancy of our continent, but also to show that all 54 countries are connected and interdependent in our common vision for a
united scientific community.
The radiating spheres express our desire for African science to be a positive force within the global scientific community,
innovative in approach and influential in resolving common world challenges.
Our stature and the importance of our role in bringing all stakeholders together is reflected in the bold but reassuring type
treatment of our name.
This is the preferred logo option and should be used first in all situations. If the application cannot support this logo for good
reason, only then should the alternative versions be considered.
